Note: ============================================================================
Note: Fast Name-to-Number Lookup
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "get_darwin_arm64_syscall_number" that takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Returns the syscall number (with 0x2000000 prefix) for a given name on Darwin ARM64
    Note: Returns -1 if the syscall name is not recognized
    Note: The numbers are identical to Darwin x86_64 (same XNU kernel table)

    If StringCore.string_equals(name, "read") is equal to 1:
        Return SYS_DARWIN_ARM64_READ
    End If
    If StringCore.string_equals(name, "write") is equal to 1:
        Return SYS_DARWIN_ARM64_WRITE
    End If
    If StringCore.string_equals(name, "open") is equal to 1:
        Return SYS_DARWIN_ARM64_OPEN
    End If
    If StringCore.string_equals(name, "close") is equal to 1:
        Return SYS_DARWIN_ARM64_CLOSE
    End If
    If StringCore.string_equals(name, "lseek") is equal to 1:
        Return SYS_DARWIN_ARM64_LSEEK
    End If
    If StringCore.string_equals(name, "openat") is equal to 1:
        Return SYS_DARWIN_ARM64_OPENAT
    End If
    If StringCore.string_equals(name, "pread") is equal to 1:
        Return SYS_DARWIN_ARM64_PREAD
    End If
    If StringCore.string_equals(name, "pwrite") is equal to 1:
        Return SYS_DARWIN_ARM64_PWRITE
    End If
    If StringCore.string_equals(name, "readv") is equal to 1:
        Return SYS_DARWIN_ARM64_READV
    End If
    If StringCore.string_equals(name, "writev") is equal to 1:
        Return SYS_DARWIN_ARM64_WRITEV
    End If
